ical-monsoon", "origin": "", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 0}, {"name": "Rama Tulsi (Krishna Tulsi) 🏆 🌏", "slug": "rama-tulsi-krishna-tulsi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India (North Central origin), cultivated 5000+ years. Most common Tulsi in Kerala homes", "traits": "Bright green leaves, sometimes with purple tinge. Grows 45-60cm tall. Forms 35cm domes. Aromatic subshrub. Strong camphor and cinnamon scent.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Continuous year-round in Kerala. Perennial that grows for years. Daily leaf picking for worship.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Universally available throughout Kerala - every nursery, temple grounds, local plant sellers, agricultural dept. Cultural staple in Kerala gardens and households.", "sort_order": 1}, {"name": "Krishna Tulsi (Shyam Tulsi) 🏆 🌏", "slug": "krishna-tulsi-shyam-tulsi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India, sacred purple variety of holy basil", "traits": "Purple-green leaves, darker than Rama Tulsi. Grows 45-60cm tall. More intense coloration.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Continuous perennial growth in Kerala tropical climate.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Kerala nurseries, temple plant distributions, agricultural centers, Ayurvedic medicine suppliers.", "sort_order": 2}, {"name": "Vana Tulsi (Wild Tulsi) 🏆 🌏", "slug": "vana-tulsi-wild-tulsi", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "origin": "India (Ocimum gratissimum), woody perennial variety", "traits": "Large, fuzzy leaves. Grows taller than other Tulsi - up to 90cm. Woody stems. Looks more like mint than typical basil.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "Woody perennial provides long-term harvest in tropical Kerala.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "", "sort_order": 3}, {"name": "Kapoor Tulsi (Temperate Tulsi) 🌏", "slug": "