": "", "yield_notes": "Fruits monsoon season, highly perishable (2 days room temp), doesn''t ripen after harvest", "growing_notes": "PERFECT FOR KERALA TROPICAL CLIMATE. Called ''Indian blackberry'' due to color but completely different plant family. Thrives in tropical/subtropical moderate-high humidity. Prefers well-drained sandy loam or clayey soil rich in organic matter. Adapts to poor rocky waterlogged soils. Ideal temp 25-35°C. Full sun best. Drought-resistant once established. Rich in antioxidants, anti-diabetic, heart health, treats hemorrhoids, anemia. Deeply embedded in Kerala culture and traditions. Available throughout monsoon at local markets.", "availability": "Widespread in Kerala - local nurseries, markets, naturally occurring. Greens of Kerala, local tree nurseries", "sort_order": 0}], "variety_count": 27}'::jsonb,
